Description: ADAPT-ME extends the ADAPT framework for longitudinal and repeated-measures
  microbiome studies. It treats zero counts as left-censored observations and fits
  mixed-effects Tobit models for log count ratios, incorporating subject-level random
  intercepts via Gauss-Hermite quadrature to account for within-subject correlation.
  Reference taxa are selected using a BUM-guided iterative procedure that incorporates
  both median fold-change distance and within-subject stability, making the method
  robust to compositional bias in paired and longitudinal designs.
